.el .ds Aq '
.TH context 1  "context " 
.SH NAME
context \- Show or set the per\-repo context (stored in regin\*(Aqs own DB, keyed by repo path)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcontext\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Show or set the per\-repo context (stored in regin\*(Aqs own DB, keyed by repo path)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
context\-show(1)
Show the stored context for the current repo
.TP
context\-set(1)
Set the stored context for the current repo
.TP
context\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
